In the message, the Prince said he is pleased to be visiting the country to launch the Great Festival of Creativity and mark the start of the Year of Cultural Exchange.

'I'm very pleased to be visiting China soon,' he said. 'Together, the United Kingdom and China have much to celebrate about our cultural relationship - what we have in common and what we can learn from one another.' 

According to The Telegraph, one user of Weibo - the Chinese equivalent of Twitter - wrote: 'It was so cute when Prince William spoke Mandarin. Could he bring his little boy to China soon?'

Another wrote: 'People always go on about his hairline, but his Chinese is great'. 

A Twitter user tweeted: 'Bloody hell watching chinese news and prince william's speaking mandarin wishing happy chinese new year!' 

