The Great Festival of Creativity will take place at Shanghai's Long Museum from March 2 to 4, with the Prince travelling to the city after spending time in Beijing.

During the Festival, British commercial creativity and innovation will be given a platform that will put it in front of a high profile business audience from the UK, China and beyond.

